Howard's Version:
1) If you open 1NT, and partner bids a 2@D/2H transfer, always jump to 3@H/3@S with 4-card support regardless of HCP.

2) If you open 2NT (or rebid 2NT after a 2@C opener), and partner bids a 3@D/3@H transfer, jump to 4@H/4@S with 4-card support.

3) When partner's transfer bid is doubled (lead directing), the NT bidder's responses are as follows:

a) With 2-card support pass. The transfer bidder can then redouble to re-transfer, or make any other appropriate bid (usually 2NT or 3NT).

b) With 3-card support, immediately accept the transfer (e.g.. bid 2@H/2@S over the 2@D/2@H transfer).

c) With 4-card support, Super-Accept.|
